{
  "description": "Canonical caller-stub contract for the .github/workflows/*.yml stubs in every member repo. Each member stub is a thin wrapper that `uses:` one of concord's reusable workflows; this file is the machine-readable source of truth for the two fields that must never drift — the `uses:` ref and the `permissions:` block. Enforced by scripts/check-workflow-stubs.py (see `make stubs-check`). Per-repo variation — `on:` triggers, `with:` inputs (curseforge-id, modrinth-id, mod-id), and concurrency — is deliberately NOT compared, so a member stays free to set them. Edit this file when a reusable workflow's required caller permissions or ref change, and keep the matching header-comment stub in the reusable workflow in step.",
